Cluster management commands

Usage:
  grainfs cluster [command]

Available Commands:
  balancer        Cluster balancer commands
  config          Inspect or change cluster-wide policy
  drain           Remove a voter via graceful transfer-leader + remove-peer composite
  events          Show recent cluster audit events
  health          Show aggregated cluster health (quorum, peers, issues)
  invite          Zero-CA invite tooling (mint one-time join invites)
  join            Join an existing cluster via KEK challenge-response handshake (offline bootstrap)
  peers           List cluster voters with leader and liveness state
  placement       Show object placement summary and detail
  remove-peer     Remove a voter from the meta-Raft cluster (joint consensus)
  rotate-key      Rolling cluster-key rotation (zero-downtime)
  status          Show cluster status (leader, term, peers)
  transfer-leader Trigger immediate leadership transfer to another voter

Flags:
      --endpoint string   admin Unix socket path (required, e.g. ./tmp/admin.sock)
      --format string     Output format: text or json (status/peers/events; ignored elsewhere) (default "text")
  -h, --help              help for cluster

Global Flags:
      --log-level string   log level: debug, info, warn, error (default "info")

Use "grainfs cluster [command] --help" for more information about a command.
